Technology\

\b0 \
This project was created with the p5.js framework. p5.js is a JavaScript library that embraces the goal of make coding accessible for artists, designers, educators, and beginners, and reinterprets it for modern web technology. It\'92s used primarily in bluerondo.com for the drawing abstractions that make working with HTML Canvas elements a breeze. p5.js also features add-on libraries that make for easy interaction with other HTML5 objects, such as web audio. Without this audio toolkit for generating useful data and handling the audio, blueron.do would not be possible. \
\
The exchange of flexibility and self-expression that P5.js allows for creative design explorations comes at a bit of a performance cost. Blueron.do works best on desktop, as most mobile devices seem unable to handle both the playback of the audio components and the updating of the canvas object.\
\
Deciding whether to create a responsive site based on proportions as opposed to pixel values seemed like the correct approach conceptually and technically, but required responsive web techniques. P5.js also handles hi-density display automatically. \
